<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 07 at 11:00PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>Black ice is likely overnight with temperatures below freezing and
mixed precipitation coming to an end from west to east. Areas that
received freezing rain will remain slick, and areas where
rain/sleet fell will refreeze into black ice over the next few
hours. Black ice should diminish closer to sunrise as temperatures
warm above freezing. Drivers should take extra care when
traveling overnight</description>
